text: GENUINE POV: I bought the iPhone XS Max the day it came out 3 years ago and it STILL takes the same quality photos as the new iPhone 13 Pro Max. I tried it at Apple store last Friday here in SF. Apple is good at sprinkling new features onto their camera but at its core most of us stick to XS Max for a reason. The inky colors and clarity is no different than the new iPhone on a normal photo. But Apple needs to make money so marketing is their best friend. PLUS I still get all day battery life (this is my primary computer), it even has zero scratches on my case-less phone and WEIRDLY enough in direct sunlight side by side my 625 nits of brightness screen was brighter than the 1000 / 1200 nits of brightness screen on the new iPhone. Even an apple employee thought that was strange. Perhaps it‚Äôs the type of screen? The new iPhone is definitely worth getting if you have an iPhone 8 or less. But just wait until there‚Äôs no notch, a usb-c and wide angle in the front camera.

text: 11:17 I really don't like that Apple uses fantasy f-numbers. The 13 Pro main camera hardware is approximately equivalent to a full frame camera with 26mm f/6.7 lens.
